#: src/building-from-source.md:118
msgid "Note to packagers"
msgstr ""

#: src/building-from-source.md:120
msgid ""
"If you are making a package of Helix for end users, to provide a good out of "
"the box experience, you should set the `HELIX_DEFAULT_RUNTIME` environment "
"variable at build time (before invoking `cargo build`) to a directory which "
"will store the final runtime files after installation. For example, say you "
"want to package the runtime into `/usr/lib/helix/runtime`. The rough steps a "
"build script could follow are:"
msgstr ""

#: src/building-from-source.md:127
msgid "`export HELIX_DEFAULT_RUNTIME=/usr/lib/helix/runtime`"
msgstr ""

#: src/building-from-source.md:128
msgid "`cargo build --profile opt --locked`"
msgstr ""

#: src/building-from-source.md:129
msgid "`cp -r runtime $BUILD_DIR/usr/lib/helix/`"
msgstr ""

#: src/building-from-source.md:130
msgid "`cp target/opt/hx $BUILD_DIR/usr/bin/hx`"
msgstr ""

#: src/building-from-source.md:132
msgid ""
"This way the resulting `hx` binary will always look for its runtime "
"directory in `/usr/lib/helix/runtime` if the user has no custom runtime in "
"`~/.config/helix` or `HELIX_RUNTIME`."
msgstr ""

